WEBVTT

00:00:16.580 --> 00:00:27.080
I. God, who at sundry times and in diverse manners spake in time past unto the fathers

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:32.660
by the prophets, hath in these last days spoken unto us by his son, whom he hath appointed

00:00:32.660 --> 00:00:36.160
heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds.

00:00:36.640 --> 00:00:41.840
Who being the brightness of his glory and the express image of his person, and upholding

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:47.620
all things by the word of his power, when he had by himself purged our sins, sat down

00:00:47.620 --> 00:00:52.540
on the right hand of the majesty on high, being made so much better than the angels,

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:56.940
as he hath by inheritance obtained a more excellent name than they.

00:00:57.620 --> 00:01:03.600
For unto which of the angels said he at any time, Thou art my son, this day have I begotten

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:04.000
thee.

00:01:04.440 --> 00:01:08.780
And again, I will be to him a father, and he shall be to me a son.

00:01:09.200 --> 00:01:14.340
And again, when he bringeth in the first begotten into the world, he sayeth, And let all the

00:01:14.340 --> 00:01:15.960
angels of God worship him.

00:01:16.340 --> 00:01:21.760
And of the angels, he sayeth, Who maketh his angels spirits, and his ministers a flame

00:01:21.760 --> 00:01:22.420
of fire.

00:01:22.860 --> 00:01:27.820
But unto the sun he sayeth, Thy throne, O God, is for ever and ever.

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:31.320
A scepter of righteousness is the scepter of thy kingdom.

00:01:31.620 --> 00:01:34.600
Thou hast loved righteousness, and hated iniquity.

00:01:34.980 --> 00:01:41.020
Therefore God, even thy God, hath anointed thee with the oil of gladness above thy fellows.

00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:46.800
And thou, Lord, in the beginning hast laid the foundation of the earth, and the heavens

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:48.700
are the works of thine hands.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:55.240
They shall perish, but thou remainest, and they shall all wax old, as doth a garment.

00:01:55.780 --> 00:02:01.460
And as a vesture shalt thou fold them up, and they shall be changed, but thou art the

00:02:01.460 --> 00:02:03.820
same, and thy years shall not fail.

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:10.000
But to which of the angels said he at any time, Sit on my right hand until I make thine

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:11.540
enemies thy footstool?

00:02:11.980 --> 00:02:17.020
Are they not all ministering spirits sent forth to minister for them who shall be heirs

00:02:17.020 --> 00:02:17.920
of salvation?

00:02:19.980 --> 00:02:23.680
Therefore we ought to give the more earnest

00:02:23.680 --> 00:02:28.260
heed to the things which we have heard, lest at any time we should let them slip.

00:02:28.540 --> 00:02:34.540
For if the word spoken by angels was steadfast, and every transgression and disobedience received

00:02:34.540 --> 00:02:40.000
a just recompense of reward, how shall we escape, if we neglect so great salvation,

00:02:40.240 --> 00:02:45.480
which at the first began to be spoken by the Lord, and was confirmed unto us by them that

00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:46.200
heard him?

00:02:46.200 --> 00:02:51.860
God also bearing them witness, both with signs and wonders, and with diverse miracles, and

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:54.760
gifts of the Holy Ghost, according to his own will.

00:02:55.240 --> 00:03:00.500
For unto the angels hath he not put in subjection the world to come, whereof we speak.

00:03:00.860 --> 00:03:07.000
But one in a certain place testified, saying, What is man, that thou art mindful of him,

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:09.840
or the son of man, that thou visitest him?

00:03:10.500 --> 00:03:15.720
Thou madeest him a little lower than the angels, thou crownedest him with glory and honour,

00:03:15.720 --> 00:03:18.840
and didst set him over the works of thy hands.

00:03:19.180 --> 00:03:22.280
Thou hast put all things in subjection under his feet.

00:03:22.740 --> 00:03:27.920
For in that he put all in subjection under him, he left nothing that is not put under

00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:28.320
him.

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:31.620
But now we see not yet all things put under him.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:36.840
But we see Jesus, who was made a little lower than the angels for the suffering of death,

00:03:37.040 --> 00:03:41.800
crowned with glory and honour, that he by the grace of God should taste death for every

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:42.220
man.

00:03:42.220 --> 00:03:48.560
For it became him, for whom are all things, and by whom are all things, in bringing many

00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:53.860
sons unto glory, to make the captain of their salvation perfect through sufferings.

00:03:54.180 --> 00:04:00.020
For both he that sanctifieth, and they who are sanctified, are all of one, for which

00:04:00.020 --> 00:04:05.920
cause he is not ashamed to call them brethren, saying, I will declare thy name unto my brethren,

00:04:06.220 --> 00:04:09.320
in the midst of the church will I sing praise unto thee.

00:04:09.660 --> 00:04:16.000
And again I will put my trust in him, and again behold I and the children which God

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:17.000
hath given me.

00:04:17.360 --> 00:04:23.140
For as much then as the children are partakers of flesh and blood, he also himself likewise

00:04:23.140 --> 00:04:27.980
took part of the same, that through death he might destroy him that had the power of

00:04:27.980 --> 00:04:33.620
death, that is, the devil, and deliver them who, through fear of death, were all their

00:04:33.620 --> 00:04:35.400
lifetimes subject to bondage.

00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:41.320
For verily he took not on him the nature of angels, but he took on him the seed of Abraham.

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:46.920
Wherefore in all things it behoved him to be made like unto his brethren, that he might

00:04:46.920 --> 00:04:52.440
be a merciful and faithful high priest in things pertaining to God, to make reconciliation

00:04:52.440 --> 00:04:54.040
for the sins of the people.

00:04:54.360 --> 00:05:00.180
For in that he himself hath suffered being tempted, he is able to succor them that are

00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:00.640
tempted.

00:05:05.820 --> 00:05:11.100
Partakers of the heavenly calling, consider the apostle and high priest of our profession

00:05:11.100 --> 00:05:17.140
Christ Jesus, who was faithful to him that appointed him, as also Moses was faithful

00:05:17.140 --> 00:05:18.320
in all his house.

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:24.160
For this man was counted worthy of more glory than Moses, inasmuch as he who hath builded

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:26.960
the house hath more honor than the house.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:32.300
For every house is builded by some man, but he that built all things is God.

00:05:32.660 --> 00:05:38.640
And Moses verily was faithful in all his house, as a servant, for a testimony of those things

00:05:38.640 --> 00:05:40.480
which were to be spoken after.

00:05:41.140 --> 00:05:47.580
But Christ as a son over his own house, whose house are we, if we hold fast the confidence

00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:50.720
and the rejoicing of the hope, firm and to the end.

00:05:51.240 --> 00:05:57.020
Wherefore, as the Holy Ghost sayeth, to-day if ye will hear his voice, harden not your

00:05:57.020 --> 00:05:57.520
hearts.

00:05:57.520 --> 00:06:02.900
As in the provocation in the day of temptation in the wilderness, when your fathers tempted

00:06:02.900 --> 00:06:06.420
me, proved me, and saw my works forty years.

00:06:06.840 --> 00:06:12.540
Wherefore I was grieved with that generation, and said, They do all way err in their heart,

00:06:12.700 --> 00:06:14.560
and they have not known my ways.

00:06:15.100 --> 00:06:19.340
So I swear in my wrath, they shall not enter into my rest.

00:06:20.100 --> 00:06:25.980
Take heed, brethren, lest there be in any of you an evil heart of unbelief in departing

00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:27.080
from the living God.

00:06:27.480 --> 00:06:32.840
But exhort one another daily, while it is called to-day, lest any of you be hardened

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:34.820
through the deceitfulness of sin.

00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:41.340
For we are made partakers of Christ, if we hold the beginning of our confidence steadfast

00:06:41.340 --> 00:06:47.760
unto the end, while it is said, to-day if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts,

00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:49.200
as in the provocation.

00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:52.600
For some, when they had heard, did provoke.

00:06:52.600 --> 00:06:55.880
How be it not all that came out of Egypt by Moses?

00:06:56.680 --> 00:06:59.120
But with whom was he grieved forty years?

00:06:59.360 --> 00:07:03.440
Was it not with them that had sinned, whose carcasses fell in the wilderness?

00:07:03.940 --> 00:07:08.880
And to whom swear he that they should not enter into his rest, but to them that believe

00:07:08.880 --> 00:07:09.500
it not?

00:07:09.500 --> 00:07:14.400
So we see that they could not enter in because of unbelief.

00:07:53.395 --> 00:08:01.055
Let us therefore fear, lest, a promise being left us of entering into his rest, any of you

00:08:01.055 --> 00:08:07.555
should seem to come short of it. For unto us was the gospel preached, as well as unto them.

00:08:08.195 --> 00:08:13.755
But the word preached did not profit them, not being mixed with faith in them that heard it.

00:08:14.435 --> 00:08:21.695
For we which have believed do enter into rest, as he said. As I have sworn in my wrath,

00:08:21.695 --> 00:08:26.795
if they shall enter into my rest, although the works were finished from the foundation of the

00:08:26.795 --> 00:08:34.455
world. For he spake in a certain place of the seventh day on this wise, and God did rest the

00:08:34.455 --> 00:08:40.915
seventh day from all his works. And in this place again if they shall enter into my rest,

00:08:41.495 --> 00:08:47.055
seeing therefore it remaineth that some must enter therein, and they to whom it was first

00:08:47.055 --> 00:08:54.755
entered not in because of unbelief. Again he limited a certain day, saying in David,

00:08:55.255 --> 00:09:03.515
Today after so long a time, as it is said, Today if ye will hear his voice, harden not your hearts.

00:09:03.915 --> 00:09:09.635
For if Jesus had given them rest, then would he not afterward have spoken of another day.

00:09:10.595 --> 00:09:17.035
There remaineth therefore a rest to the people of God. For he that is entered into his rest,

00:09:17.055 --> 00:09:24.755
he also hath ceased from his own works, as God did from his. Let us labor therefore to enter

00:09:24.755 --> 00:09:31.935
into that rest, lest any man fall after the same example of unbelief. For the word of God is quick

00:09:31.935 --> 00:09:39.175
and powerful, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the dividing asunder

00:09:39.175 --> 00:09:46.215
of soul and spirit, and of the joints and marrow, and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents

00:09:46.215 --> 00:09:52.495
of the heart. Neither is there any creature that is not manifest in his sight, but all things are

00:09:52.495 --> 00:09:59.915
naked and open unto the eyes of him with whom we have to do. Seeing then that we have a great high

00:09:59.915 --> 00:10:06.655
priest that is passed into the heavens, Jesus the Son of God, let us hold fast our profession.

00:10:07.715 --> 00:10:13.495
For we have not an high priest which cannot be touched with the feeling of our infirmities,

00:10:13.995 --> 00:10:22.195
but was in all points tempted like as we are, yet without sin. Let us therefore come boldly

00:10:22.195 --> 00:10:28.915
unto the throne of grace, that we may obtain mercy and find grace to help in time of need.

00:10:29.335 --> 00:10:37.315
For every high priest taken from among men is ordained for men in things pertaining to

00:10:37.315 --> 00:10:44.715
God, that he may offer both gifts and sacrifices for sins, who can have compassion on the ignorant

00:10:44.715 --> 00:10:50.935
and on them that are out of the way, for that he himself is also compassed with infirmity.

00:10:51.275 --> 00:10:58.095
And by reason hereof he ought, as for the people, so also for himself to offer for sins.

00:10:58.255 --> 00:11:05.055
And no man taketh this honor unto himself, but he that is called of God, as was Aaron.

00:11:05.755 --> 00:11:12.415
So also Christ glorified not himself to be made an high priest, but he that said unto him,

00:11:12.775 --> 00:11:20.435
Thou art my son, today have I begotten thee. As he sayeth also in another place,

00:11:21.015 --> 00:11:26.815
Thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek, who in the days of his flesh,

00:11:27.155 --> 00:11:33.175
when he had offered up prayers and supplications with strong crying and tears unto him that was

00:11:33.175 --> 00:11:38.775
able to save him from death, and was heard in that he feared, though he were a son,

00:11:39.195 --> 00:11:44.535
yet learned he obedience by the things which he suffered. And, being made perfect,

00:11:44.935 --> 00:11:51.495
he became the author of eternal salvation unto all them that obey him, called of God

00:11:51.495 --> 00:11:59.355
and high priest after the order of Melchizedek, of whom we have many things to say, and hard

00:11:59.355 --> 00:12:05.975
to be uttered, seeing ye are dull of hearing. For when, for the time ye ought to be teachers,

00:12:06.515 --> 00:12:12.395
ye have need that one teach you again, which be the first principles of the oracles of God,

00:12:13.155 --> 00:12:20.595
and are become such as have need of milk and not of strong meat. For every one that useth

00:12:20.595 --> 00:12:28.215
milk is unskillful in the word of righteousness, for he is a babe, but strong meat belongeth to

00:12:28.215 --> 00:12:35.035
them that are of full age, even those who by reason of use have their senses exercised

00:12:35.035 --> 00:12:40.055
to discern both good and evil

00:12:41.195 --> 00:12:47.215
Therefore, leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto perfection,

00:12:47.835 --> 00:12:52.795
not laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God.

00:12:56.735 --> 00:13:00.515
and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead,

00:13:00.975 --> 00:13:08.375
and of eternal judgment. And this will we do, if God permit. For it is impossible for those who

00:13:08.375 --> 00:13:14.015
were once enlightened, and have tasted of the heavenly gift, and were made partakers of the

00:13:14.015 --> 00:13:19.695
Holy Ghost, and have tasted the good word of God, and the powers of the world to come,

00:13:20.175 --> 00:13:27.295
if they shall fall away, to renew them again unto repentance, seeing they crucify to themselves

00:13:27.295 --> 00:13:34.435
the Son of God afresh, and put him to an open shame. For the earth which drinketh in the rain,

00:13:34.935 --> 00:13:41.595
that cometh oft upon it, and bringeth forth herbs, meat for them by whom it is dressed,

00:13:42.315 --> 00:13:48.215
receiveth blessing from God. But that which beareth thorns and briars is rejected,

00:13:48.215 --> 00:13:56.175
and is nigh unto cursing, whose end is to be burned. But beloved, we are persuaded

00:13:56.175 --> 00:14:03.415
better things of you, and things that accompany salvation, though we thus speak. For God is not

00:14:03.415 --> 00:14:09.155
unrighteous to forget your work, and labor of love, which ye have shewed toward his name,

00:14:09.795 --> 00:14:15.715
in that ye have ministered to the saints, and do minister. And we desire that every one of you

00:14:15.715 --> 00:14:23.735
do shew the same diligence to the full assurance of hope unto the end, that ye be not slothful,

00:14:23.955 --> 00:14:28.855
but followers of them who through faith and patience inherit the promises.

00:14:29.815 --> 00:14:36.415
For when God made promise to Abraham, because he could swear by no greater, he swear by himself,

00:14:36.775 --> 00:14:43.795
saying, Surely blessing I will bless thee, and multiplying I will multiply thee. And so,

00:14:43.795 --> 00:14:50.075
after he had patiently endured, he obtained the promise. For men barely swear by the greater,

00:14:50.455 --> 00:14:57.295
and an oath for confirmation is to them an end of all strife. Where in God, willing more abundantly

00:14:57.295 --> 00:15:03.915
to shew unto the heirs of promise the immutability of his counsel, confirmed it by an oath, that by

00:15:03.915 --> 00:15:10.795
two immutable things, in which it was impossible for God to lie, we might have a strong consolation,

00:15:10.795 --> 00:15:15.675
who have fled for refuge, to lay hold upon the hope set before us,

00:15:16.175 --> 00:15:23.495
which hope we have as an anchor of the soul, both sure and steadfast, and which entereth

00:15:23.495 --> 00:15:31.815
into that within the veil. Whither the forerunner is for us entered, even Jesus made an high priest

00:15:31.815 --> 00:15:37.875
forever after the order of Melchizedek.

00:16:10.816 --> 00:16:18.216
For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the Most High God, who met Abraham,

00:16:18.636 --> 00:16:25.896
returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him, to whom also Abraham gave a tenth

00:16:25.896 --> 00:16:35.796
part of all, first being by interpretation king of righteousness, and after that also king of Salem,

00:16:35.796 --> 00:16:43.796
which is king of peace, without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning

00:16:43.796 --> 00:16:52.476
of days nor end of life, but made like unto the Son of God, abideth a priest continually.

00:16:53.136 --> 00:17:01.676
Now consider how great this man was, unto whom even the patriarch Abraham gave the tenth of the

00:17:02.276 --> 00:17:10.496
And verily, they that are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a

00:17:10.496 --> 00:17:19.776
commandment, to take tithes of the people according to the law, that is, of their brethren, though they

00:17:19.776 --> 00:17:28.236
come out of the loins of Abraham, but he whose descent is not counted from them, received tithes

00:17:28.236 --> 00:17:37.456
of Abraham, and blessed him that had the promises, and without all contradiction, the less is blessed

00:17:37.456 --> 00:17:47.116
of the better. And here men that die receive tithes, but there he receiveth them, of whom it is

00:17:47.116 --> 00:18:00.276
that he liveth, and as I may so say, Levi also who receiveth tithes, paid tithes in Abraham, for he was

00:18:00.276 --> 00:18:08.016
yet in the loins of his father when Melchizedek met him. If therefore perfection were by the

00:18:08.016 --> 00:18:15.336
Levitical priesthood, for under it the people received the law, what further need was there that

00:18:15.336 --> 00:18:22.656
another priest should rise after the order of Melchizedek, and not be called after the order of Aaron?

00:18:22.976 --> 00:18:32.076
For the priesthood being changed, there is made of necessity a change also of the law, for he of whom these

00:18:32.076 --> 00:18:41.396
things are spoken pertaineth to another tribe, of which no man gave attendance at the altar, for it is

00:18:41.396 --> 00:18:49.556
evident that our Lord sprang out of Judah, of which tribe Moses spake nothing concerning priesthood.

00:18:49.856 --> 00:18:59.496
And it is yet far more evident, for that after the similitude of Melchizedek, there ariseth another priest,

00:19:00.036 --> 00:19:07.396
who is made not after the law of a carnal commandment, but after the power of an endless life.

00:19:08.006 --> 00:19:17.796
For he testifieth, thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek, for there is verily a

00:19:17.796 --> 00:19:24.716
disannulling of the commandment going before, for the weakness and unprofitableness thereof,

00:19:24.996 --> 00:19:32.976
for the law made nothing perfect, but the bringing in of a better hope did by the

00:19:32.976 --> 00:19:43.416
law, which we draw nigh unto God. And inasmuch as not without an oath, he was made priest, for those

00:19:43.416 --> 00:19:53.076
priests were made without an oath, but this with an oath by him that said unto him, The Lord swear

00:19:53.076 --> 00:20:01.536
and will not repent, thou art a priest forever after the order of Melchizedek. By so much was

00:20:01.536 --> 00:20:10.116
made a surety of a better testament, and they truly were many priests, because they were not

00:20:10.116 --> 00:20:18.576
suffered to continue by reason of death. But this man, because he continueth ever, hath an

00:20:18.576 --> 00:20:27.176
unchangeable priesthood, wherefore he is able also to save them to the uttermost that come unto God

00:20:27.176 --> 00:20:35.896
by him, seeing he ever liveth to make intercession for them. For such an high priest became us,

00:20:35.896 --> 00:20:44.196
who is holy, harmless, undefiled, separate from sinners, and made higher than the heavens,

00:20:45.236 --> 00:20:51.996
who needeth not daily as those high priests to offer up sacrifice, first for his own sins,

00:20:51.996 --> 00:21:00.396
and then for the people's. For this he did once, when he offered up himself. For the law maketh

00:21:00.396 --> 00:21:07.936
men high priests which have infirmity, but the word of the oath which was since the law maketh

00:21:07.936 --> 00:21:17.876
the son who is consecrated forevermore. Now, of the things which we have spoken,

00:21:17.876 --> 00:21:25.776
this is the sum. We have such an high priest, who is set on the right hand of the throne of

00:21:25.776 --> 00:21:34.036
the majesty in the heavens, a minister of the sanctuary, and of the true tabernacle which the

00:21:34.036 --> 00:21:41.956
Lord pitched, and not man. For every high priest is ordained to offer gifts and sacrifices, wherefore

00:21:41.956 --> 00:21:51.536
it is of necessity that this man have somewhat also to offer. For if he were on earth, he should

00:21:51.536 --> 00:21:58.936
not be a priest, seeing that there are priests that offer gifts according to the law, who serve

00:21:58.936 --> 00:22:06.316
unto the example and shadow of heavenly things, as Moses was admonished of God when he was about

00:22:06.316 --> 00:22:14.356
to make the tabernacle. For see, saith he, that thou make all things according to the pattern

00:22:14.356 --> 00:22:23.376
shewed to thee in the mount. But now hath he obtained a more excellent ministry, by how much

00:22:23.376 --> 00:22:33.016
also he is the mediator of a better covenant, which was established upon better promises. For

00:22:33.016 --> 00:22:39.436
if that first covenant had been faultless, then should no place have been sought for the second.

00:22:40.096 --> 00:22:46.596
For finding fault with them, he said, Behold, the days come, saith the Lord, when I will make

00:22:46.596 --> 00:22:53.536
a new covenant with the house of Israel, and with the house of Judah. Not according to the covenant

00:22:53.536 --> 00:23:00.376
that I made with their fathers, in the day when I took them by the hand to lead them out of the land

00:23:00.376 --> 00:23:09.016
of Egypt, because they continued not in my covenant, and I regarded them not, saith the Lord. For this is

00:23:09.016 --> 00:23:15.336
the covenant that I will make with the house of Israel, after those days, saith the Lord. I will

00:23:15.336 --> 00:23:22.716
put my laws into their mind, and write them in their hearts, and I will be to them a God, and they

00:23:22.716 --> 00:23:30.996
shall be to me a people. And they shall not teach every man his neighbor, and every man his brother,

00:23:31.316 --> 00:23:38.676
saying, Know the Lord, for all shall know me, from the least to the greatest. For I will be merciful

00:23:38.676 --> 00:23:47.116
to their unrighteousness, and their sins and their iniquities will I remember no more. In that he

00:23:47.886 --> 00:23:57.256
covenant he hath made the first old, now that which decayeth and waxeth old is ready to vanish away.

00:23:58.376 --> 00:24:08.076
Then verily, the first covenant had also ordinances of divine service, and a worldly

00:24:08.076 --> 00:24:15.436
sanctuary. For there was a tabernacle made, the first wherein was the candlestick, and the table,

00:24:15.436 --> 00:24:23.116
and the showbread, which is called the sanctuary. And after the second veil, the tabernacle,

00:24:23.456 --> 00:24:30.836
which is called the holiest of all, which had the golden censer, and the ark of the covenant,

00:24:31.316 --> 00:24:39.316
overlaid round about with gold, wherein was the golden pot that had manna, and Aaron's rod that

00:24:39.316 --> 00:24:48.656
it, and the tables of the covenant. And over it the cherubims of glory, shadowing the mercy seat

00:24:48.656 --> 00:24:56.136
of which we cannot now speak particularly. Now, when these things were thus ordained,

00:24:56.476 --> 00:25:04.146
the priest went always into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the service of God. But into the

00:25:04.146 --> 00:25:11.066
second went the high priest alone, once every year, not without blood, which he offered for

00:25:11.066 --> 00:25:19.126
himself, and for the errors of the people. The Holy Ghost this signifying that the way into the

00:25:19.126 --> 00:25:28.606
holiest of all was not yet made manifest, while as the first tabernacle was yet standing. Which was

00:25:28.606 --> 00:25:36.426
a figure for the time then present, in which were offered both gifts and sacrifices, that could not

00:25:36.426 --> 00:25:44.546
make him that did the service perfect. As pertaining to the conscience, which stood only in meats and

00:25:44.546 --> 00:25:52.586
drinks and divers washings, and carnal ordinances imposed on them until the time of reformation.

00:25:52.586 --> 00:26:00.106
But Christ, being come in high priest of good things to come, by a greater and more perfect

00:26:00.106 --> 00:26:07.826
tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this building, neither by the blood of goats

00:26:07.826 --> 00:26:16.466
and calves, but by his own blood, he entered in once into the Holy Place, having obtained

00:26:16.466 --> 00:26:26.026
eternal redemption for us. For if the blood of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of in heifer

00:26:26.026 --> 00:26:33.906
sprinkling the unclean sanctified to the purifying of the flesh, how much more shall the blood of

00:26:33.906 --> 00:26:41.626
Christ, who through the eternal spirit offered himself without spot to God, purge your conscience

00:26:41.626 --> 00:26:50.506
from dead works to serve the living God. And for this cause, he is the mediator of the New Testament,

00:26:50.966 --> 00:26:56.786
that by means of death, for the redemption of the transgressions that were under the first

00:26:56.786 --> 00:27:11.606
testament, they which are called might receive the promise of eternal inheritance. For where a

00:27:11.606 --> 00:27:20.646
death of the testator, for a testament is a force after men are dead, otherwise it is of no strength,

00:27:21.186 --> 00:27:28.526
at all, while the testator liveth, whereupon neither the first testament was dedicated with

00:27:28.526 --> 00:27:35.706
our blood. For when Moses had spoken every precept to all the people, according to the law, he took

00:27:35.706 --> 00:27:44.226
the blood of calves and of goats with water and scarlet wool and hyssop, and sprinkled both the book

00:27:44.226 --> 00:27:52.826
and all the people, saying, This is the blood of the testament which God hath enjoined unto you.

00:27:53.366 --> 00:28:00.106
Moreover, he sprinkled with blood both the tabernacle and all the vessels of the ministry,

00:28:00.106 --> 00:28:08.546
and almost all things are by the law purged with blood, and without shedding of blood

00:28:08.546 --> 00:28:17.926
there is no remission. It was therefore necessary that the patterns of things in the heavens should

00:28:17.926 --> 00:28:25.386
be purified with these, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.

00:28:25.386 --> 00:28:33.046
For Christ is not entered into the holy places made with hands, which are the figures of the true,

00:28:33.346 --> 00:28:41.606
but into heaven itself now to appear in the presence of God for us. Nor yet that he should

00:28:41.606 --> 00:28:49.046
offer himself often, as the high priest entereth into the holy place every year with blood of

00:28:49.046 --> 00:28:56.286
others. For then must he often have suffered since the foundation of the world, but now once

00:28:56.286 --> 00:29:03.906
in the end of the world hath he appeared to put away sin by the sacrifice of himself.

00:29:04.446 --> 00:29:14.926
And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment. So Christ was once offered

00:29:14.926 --> 00:29:22.586
to bear the sins of many, and unto them that look for him shall he appear the second time without

00:29:22.586 --> 00:29:32.406
sin unto salvation.

00:29:45.513 --> 00:29:46.073
10.

00:30:00.453 --> 00:30:06.373
For the law, having a shadow of good things to come, and not the very image of the things,

00:30:06.373 --> 00:30:11.333
can never with those sacrifices, which they offered year by year continually,

00:30:12.033 --> 00:30:17.933
make the comers their unto perfect. For then would they not have ceased to be offered,

00:30:18.693 --> 00:30:24.153
because that the worshippers, once purged, should have had no more conscience of sins.

00:30:25.193 --> 00:30:33.173
But in those sacrifices there is a remembrance, again, made of sins every year. For it is not

00:30:33.173 --> 00:30:39.973
possible that the blood of bulls and of goats should take away sins. Wherefore,

00:30:40.593 --> 00:30:46.593
when he cometh into the world, he sayeth, Sacrifice an offering thou wouldest not,

00:30:47.173 --> 00:30:54.013
but a body hast thou prepared me. In burnt offerings and sacrifices for sin

00:30:54.013 --> 00:31:03.153
thou hast had no pleasure. Then said I, Lo, I come. In the volume of the book it is written of me.

00:31:03.693 --> 00:31:10.813
To do thy will, O God. Above when he said, Sacrifice an offering,

00:31:11.153 --> 00:31:18.253
and burnt offerings, and offering for sin, thou wouldest not, neither hadst pleasure therein,

00:31:19.113 --> 00:31:26.753
which are offered by the law. Then said he, Lo, I come to do thy will, O God. He taketh away the

00:31:26.753 --> 00:31:33.753
first, that he may establish the second, by the which will we are sanctified through the

00:31:33.753 --> 00:31:40.733
offering of the body of Jesus Christ once for all. And every priest standeth daily ministering

00:31:40.733 --> 00:31:48.893
and offering oftentimes the same sacrifices, which can never take away sins. But this man,

00:31:49.213 --> 00:31:56.033
after he had offered one sacrifice for sins forever, sat down on the right hand of God,

00:31:56.033 --> 00:32:03.313
from henceforth expecting till his enemies be made his footstool. For by one offering

00:32:03.313 --> 00:32:13.233
he hath perfected forever them that are sanctified. Whereof the Holy Ghost also is a witness to us.

00:32:13.553 --> 00:32:19.333
For after that he had said before, This is the covenant that I will make with them after those

00:32:19.333 --> 00:32:26.393
days, saith the Lord, I will put my laws into their hearts, and in their minds will I write them,

00:32:27.673 --> 00:32:31.673
and their sins and iniquities will I remember no more.

00:32:33.693 --> 00:32:39.453
Now where remission of these is, there is no more offering for sin,

00:32:41.753 --> 00:32:47.913
having therefore brethren boldness to enter into the holiest by the blood of Jesus,

00:32:48.773 --> 00:32:55.333
by a new and living way, which he hath consecrated for us through the veil,

00:32:55.813 --> 00:33:01.853
that is to say his flesh, and having an high priest over the house of God,

00:33:02.633 --> 00:33:09.193
let us draw near with a true heart in full assurance of faith, having our hearts sprinkled

00:33:09.863 --> 00:33:14.653
from an evil conscience, and our bodies washed with pure water.

00:33:15.953 --> 00:33:23.573
Let us hold fast the profession of our faith without wavering, for he is faithful that promised,

00:33:24.293 --> 00:33:31.733
and let us consider one another to provoke unto love and to good works, not forsaking

00:33:31.733 --> 00:33:38.093
the assembling of ourselves together as the manner of some is, but exhorting one another,

00:33:38.773 --> 00:33:41.893
and so much the more as ye see the day approaching.

00:33:43.113 --> 00:33:48.973
For if we sin willfully, after that we have received the knowledge of the truth,

00:33:49.173 --> 00:33:55.993
there remaineth no more sacrifice for sins, but a certain fearful looking for of judgment,

00:33:56.593 --> 00:34:01.313
and fiery indignation, which shall devour the adversaries.

00:34:02.093 --> 00:34:08.653
He that despised Moses' law died without mercy under two or three witnesses.

00:34:09.933 --> 00:34:16.973
Of how much sorer punishment, suppose ye, shall he be thought worthy, who hath trodden underfoot

00:34:16.973 --> 00:34:22.713
the Son of God, and hath counted the blood of the covenant wherewith he was sanctified,

00:34:23.013 --> 00:34:28.183
an unholy thing, and hath done despite unto the Spirit of grace.

00:34:29.543 --> 00:34:37.203
For we know him that hath said, Vengeance belongeth unto me, I will recompense,

00:34:37.463 --> 00:34:40.903
saith the Lord, and again the Lord shall judge his people.

00:34:41.743 --> 00:34:46.003
It is a fearful thing to fall into the hands of the living God,

00:34:47.403 --> 00:34:55.863
but call to remembrance the former days, in which after ye were illuminated ye endured a great

00:34:55.863 --> 00:35:04.063
fight of afflictions, partly whilst ye were made a gazing-stock both by reproaches and afflictions,

00:35:04.303 --> 00:35:08.783
and partly whilst ye became companions of them that were so used.

00:35:09.283 --> 00:35:16.183
For ye had compassion of me and my bonds, and took joyfully the spoiling of your goods,

00:35:16.563 --> 00:35:22.063
knowing in yourselves that ye have in heaven a better and an enduring substance.

00:35:23.443 --> 00:35:28.943
Cast not away, therefore, your confidence, which hath great recompense of reward,

00:35:29.403 --> 00:35:36.623
for ye have need of patience, that after ye have done the will of God, ye might receive the promise,

00:35:37.363 --> 00:35:43.923
for yet a little while, and he that shall come will come, and will not tarry.

00:35:44.883 --> 00:35:52.043
Now the just shall live by faith, but if any man draw back, my soul shall have no place in the

00:35:52.043 --> 00:36:00.363
pleasure in him. But we are not of them who draw back unto perdition, but of them that believe

00:36:01.063 --> 00:36:04.403
to the saving of the soul

00:36:05.243 --> 00:36:12.243
Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen,

00:36:12.943 --> 00:36:20.043
for by it the elders obtained a good report. Through faith we understand that the worlds

00:36:20.043 --> 00:36:27.343
were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were not made of things which do

00:36:27.343 --> 00:36:34.423
appear. By faith Abel offered unto God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, by which he

00:36:34.423 --> 00:36:41.763
obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts, and by it he being

00:36:41.763 --> 00:36:49.303
dead yet speaketh. By faith Enoch was translated that he should not see death,

00:36:50.603 --> 00:36:57.183
and was not found because God had translated him, for before his translation he had this testimony,

00:36:57.623 --> 00:37:05.363
that he pleased God. But without faith it is impossible to please him, for he that cometh

00:37:05.363 --> 00:37:12.243
to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.

00:37:12.963 --> 00:37:21.803
By faith Noah, being warned of God of things not seen as yet, moved with fear, prepared an ark to

00:37:21.803 --> 00:37:29.343
the saving of his house, by the which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness

00:37:29.343 --> 00:37:38.763
which is by faith. By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should

00:37:38.763 --> 00:37:45.823
after receive for an inheritance, obeyed, and he went out, not knowing whither he went. By faith

00:37:45.823 --> 00:37:52.143
he sojourned in the land of promise, as in a strange country, dwelling in tabernacles with

00:37:52.143 --> 00:37:59.143
Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise, for he looked for a city with

00:37:59.143 --> 00:38:07.323
foundations whose builder and maker is God. Through faith also Sarah herself received strength to

00:38:07.323 --> 00:38:15.203
conceive seed, and was delivered of a child when she was past age, because she judged him faithful

00:38:15.203 --> 00:38:23.503
who had promised, therefore sprang there even of one and him as good as dead, so many as the stars

00:38:23.503 --> 00:38:32.723
of the sky in multitude, and as the sand which is by the seashore innumerable. These all died in faith,

00:38:33.123 --> 00:38:40.503
not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off, and were persuaded of them

00:38:40.503 --> 00:38:47.863
and embraced them, and confessed that they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth.

00:38:49.643 --> 00:38:55.423
For they that say such things declare plainly that they seek a country, and truly,

00:38:56.523 --> 00:39:01.603
if they had been mindful of that country from whence they came out, they might have had

00:39:01.603 --> 00:39:09.043
opportunity to have returned, but now they desire a better country, that is, and heavenly,

00:39:09.883 --> 00:39:16.163
wherefore God is not ashamed to be called their God, for he hath prepared for them a city.

00:39:16.463 --> 00:39:24.503
By faith Abraham, when he was tried, offered up Isaac, and he that had received the promises

00:39:24.503 --> 00:39:31.703
offered up his only begotten son, of whom it was said that an Isaac shall thy seed be called,

00:39:32.623 --> 00:39:38.843
accounting that God was able to raise him up even from the dead from whence also he received him

00:39:38.843 --> 00:39:46.523
a figure. By faith Isaac blessed Jacob, and Esau concerning things to come. By faith Jacob,

00:39:46.883 --> 00:39:54.203
when he was dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph, and worshiped, leaning upon the top of his staff.

00:39:55.463 --> 00:40:01.523
By faith Joseph, when he died, made mention of the departing of the children of Israel,

00:40:01.523 --> 00:40:07.803
and gave commandment concerning his bones. By faith Moses, when he was born,

00:40:08.563 --> 00:40:13.583
was hid three months of his parents, because they saw he was a proper child,

00:40:14.463 --> 00:40:22.143
and they were not afraid of the king's commandment. By faith Moses, when he was come to years,

00:40:22.743 --> 00:40:27.723
refused to be called the son of Pharaoh's daughter, choosing rather to suffer affliction

00:40:27.723 --> 00:40:32.163
with the people of God than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a season,

00:40:32.943 --> 00:40:40.323
esteeming the reproach of Christ greater riches than the treasures in Egypt, for he had respect

00:40:40.323 --> 00:40:48.623
unto the recompense of the reward. By faith he forsook Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king,

00:40:48.843 --> 00:40:56.923
for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible. Through faith he kept the Passover, and the

00:40:56.923 --> 00:41:03.663
sprinkling of blood, lest he that destroyed the firstborn should touch them. By faith they

00:41:03.663 --> 00:41:10.443
passed through the Red Sea as by dry land, which the Egyptians, a saying to do, were drowned.

00:41:11.783 --> 00:41:18.223
By faith the walls of Jericho fell down, after they were compassed about seven days. By faith

00:41:18.223 --> 00:41:24.623
the harlot Rahab perished not with them that believed not, when she had received the spies

00:41:24.623 --> 00:41:32.303
with peace. And what shall I more say? For the time would fail me to tell of Gideon,

00:41:32.403 --> 00:41:40.663
and of Barak, and of Samson, and of Jephthah, of David also, and Samuel, and of the prophets,

00:41:41.483 --> 00:41:46.503
who through faith subdued kingdoms, wrought righteousness, obtained promises,

00:41:47.083 --> 00:41:52.903
stopped the mouths of lions, quenched the violence of fire, escaped the edge of the sword.

00:41:53.543 --> 00:42:01.523
Out of weakness were made strong, waxed valiant in fight, turned to flight the armies of the aliens.

00:42:02.363 --> 00:42:09.423
Women received their dead raised to life again. And others were tortured, not accepting deliverance,

00:42:09.623 --> 00:42:16.583
that they might obtain a better resurrection. And others had trial of cruel mockings,

00:42:16.583 --> 00:42:23.663
and scourgings, yea moreover of bonds and imprisonment. They were stoned, they were

00:42:23.663 --> 00:42:31.683
sawn asunder, were tempted, were slain with the sword. They wandered about in sheepskins and

00:42:31.683 --> 00:42:40.583
goatskins, being destitute, afflicted, tormented, of whom the world was not worthy. They wandered

00:42:40.583 --> 00:42:48.043
in deserts, and in mountains, and in dens, and caves of the earth. And these all,

00:42:48.063 --> 00:42:55.343
having obtained a good report through faith, received not the promise, God having provided

00:42:55.343 --> 00:43:01.683
some better thing for us, that they without us should not be made perfect.

00:43:11.203 --> 00:43:11.903
you

00:43:35.256 --> 00:43:40.056
12 Wherefore, seeing we also are encompassed about with so great a cloud of witnesses,

00:43:40.056 --> 00:43:45.516
let us lay aside every weight and the sin which does so easily beset us,

00:43:45.636 --> 00:43:49.636
and let us run with patience the race that is set before us.

00:43:50.156 --> 00:43:53.556
13 Looking unto Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith,

00:43:54.056 --> 00:43:59.036
who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame,

00:43:59.196 --> 00:44:02.616
and is set down at the right hand of the throne of God.

00:44:03.036 --> 00:44:07.076
14 For consider him that endured such contradiction of sinners against himself,

00:44:07.696 --> 00:44:10.216
lest ye be wearied and faint in your minds.

00:44:10.776 --> 00:44:14.756
15 Ye have not yet resisted unto blood, striving against sin.

00:44:14.936 --> 00:44:20.836
16 And ye have forgotten the exhortation which speaketh unto you as unto children, my son,

00:44:21.176 --> 00:44:26.516
despise not thou the chastening of the Lord, nor faint when thou art rebuked of him.

00:44:26.816 --> 00:44:32.336
17 For whom the Lord loveth, he chastineth, and scourgeth every son whom he receiveth.

00:44:32.336 --> 00:44:36.996
18 If ye endure chastening, God dealeth with you as with sons,

00:44:37.136 --> 00:44:40.496
for what son is he whom the Father chastineth not?

00:44:40.996 --> 00:44:45.096
19 But if ye be without chastisement, whereof all our partakers,

00:44:45.396 --> 00:44:47.716
then are ye bastards and not sons?

00:44:48.376 --> 00:44:54.276
20 Furthermore, we have had fathers of our flesh, which corrected us, and we gave them reverence,

00:44:54.576 --> 00:44:58.976
shall we not much rather be in subjection unto the Father of Spirits and live?

00:44:59.696 --> 00:45:04.056
21 For they verily for a few days chastened us after their own pleasure,

00:45:04.416 --> 00:45:08.616
but he for our profit, that we might be partakers of his holiness.

00:45:08.936 --> 00:45:13.836
22 Now no chastening for the present seemeth to be joyous, but grievous.

00:45:14.716 --> 00:45:19.556
Nevertheless afterward it yieldeth the peaceable fruit of righteousness unto them,

00:45:19.876 --> 00:45:21.656
which are exercised thereby.

00:45:22.036 --> 00:45:26.136
23 Wherefore lift up the hands which hang down, and the feeble knees,

00:45:26.136 --> 00:45:31.576
and make straight paths for your feet, lest that which is laying be turned out of the way,

00:45:31.836 --> 00:45:33.616
but let it rather be healed.

00:45:34.456 --> 00:45:39.816
24 Follow peace with all men, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord.

00:45:40.256 --> 00:45:45.796
25 Looking diligently, lest any man fail of the grace of God, lest any root of bitterness,

00:45:45.876 --> 00:45:49.736
bringing up trouble you, and thereby many be defiled.

00:45:50.416 --> 00:45:57.356
Lest there be any fornicator or profane person as Esau, who for one more slim meat sold his

00:45:57.356 --> 00:46:02.576
birthright. For ye know how that afterward, when he would have inherited the blessing,

00:46:02.796 --> 00:46:08.036
he was rejected, for he found no place of repentance, though he sought it carefully

00:46:08.036 --> 00:46:13.876
with tears. For ye are not come unto the mouth that might be touched, and that burnt with fire,

00:46:13.876 --> 00:46:19.576
nor unto blackness, and darkness, and tempest, and the sound of a trumpet, and the voice of

00:46:19.576 --> 00:46:24.396
words, which voiced they, that heard and treated, that the word should not be spoken to them

00:46:24.396 --> 00:46:29.976
any more. For they could not endure that which was commanded, and if so much as a beast touch

00:46:29.976 --> 00:46:36.056
the mountain, it shall be stoned, or thrust through with a dart. And so terrible was the

00:46:36.056 --> 00:46:42.576
sight that Moses said, I exceedingly fear and quake. But ye are come unto Mount Sion,

00:46:42.576 --> 00:46:48.556
and unto the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to an innumerable company of angels,

00:46:48.996 --> 00:46:53.296
to the general assembly and church of the firstborn, which are written in heaven,

00:46:53.416 --> 00:46:59.416
and to God the judge of all, and to the spirits of just men made perfect, and to Jesus the mediator

00:46:59.416 --> 00:47:05.336
of the new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling, that speaketh better things than that of Abel.

00:47:05.516 --> 00:47:11.296
See that ye refuse not him that speaketh, for if they escape not who refused him that spake on earth,

00:47:11.296 --> 00:47:16.096
much more shall not we escape, if we turn away from him that speaketh from heaven,

00:47:16.656 --> 00:47:22.156
whose voice then shook the earth. But now he hath promised saying, yet once more I shake not the

00:47:22.156 --> 00:47:29.376
earth only, but also heaven. And this word yet once more signifyeth the removing of those things

00:47:29.376 --> 00:47:35.316
that are shaken, as of things that are made, that those things which cannot be shaken may remain.

00:47:35.836 --> 00:47:41.276
Wherefore we receiving a kingdom which cannot be moved, let us have grace whereby we may

00:47:41.276 --> 00:47:47.756
serve God acceptably, with reverence and godly fear. For our God is a consuming fire.

00:47:49.376 --> 00:47:58.096
Let brotherly love continue. Be not forgetful to entertain strangers, for thereby

00:47:58.096 --> 00:48:04.736
some have entertained angels unawares. Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them,

00:48:04.816 --> 00:48:10.276
and them which suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body. Marriage is

00:48:10.276 --> 00:48:16.156
horrible in all, and the bed undefiled, but whoremongers and adulterers God will judge.

00:48:16.776 --> 00:48:22.276
Let your conversation be without covetousness, and be content with such things as ye have,

00:48:22.516 --> 00:48:28.236
for he hath said, I will never leave thee nor forsake thee. So that we may boldly say,

00:48:28.376 --> 00:48:34.316
The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me. Remember them which have

00:48:34.316 --> 00:48:40.636
ruled over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God, whose faith follow, considering the end

00:48:40.636 --> 00:48:48.196
of their conversation. Jesus Christ, the same yesterday, and today, and forever. Be not carried

00:48:48.196 --> 00:48:53.456
about with divers and strange doctrines, for it is a good thing that the heart be established

00:48:53.456 --> 00:49:03.116
with grace, not with meat, which have not profited them that have been occupied therein. We have an

00:49:03.116 --> 00:49:09.056
tabernacle. For the bodies of those beasts, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high

00:49:09.056 --> 00:49:15.056
priest for sin, are burned without the camp. Wherefore, Jesus also, that he might sanctify

00:49:15.056 --> 00:49:20.516
the people with his own blood, suffered without the gate. Let us go forth therefore unto him

00:49:20.516 --> 00:49:27.476
without the camp, bearing his reproach. For here we have no continuing city, but we seek one to come.

00:49:28.036 --> 00:49:33.656
By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of

00:49:33.656 --> 00:49:40.396
our lips giving thanks to his name. But to do good and to communicate forget not, for with such

00:49:40.396 --> 00:49:46.496
sacrifices God is well pleased. Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves,

00:49:46.816 --> 00:49:52.896
for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy and

00:49:52.896 --> 00:49:59.776
not with grief. For that is unprofitable for you. Pray for us, for we trust we have a good conscience

00:49:59.776 --> 00:50:05.696
in all things willing to live honestly. But I beseech you the rather to do this, that I may be

00:50:05.696 --> 00:50:12.016
restored to you the sooner. Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus,

00:50:12.416 --> 00:50:16.156
that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,

00:50:16.736 --> 00:50:22.276
make you perfect in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is well pleasing

00:50:22.276 --> 00:50:30.456
in his sight through Jesus Christ, to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen. And I beseech you,

00:50:30.636 --> 00:50:35.396
brethren, suffer the word of exhortation, for I have written a letter unto you in few words.

00:50:35.856 --> 00:50:42.776
Know ye that our brother Timothy is set at liberty, with whom if he come shortly I will see you.

00:50:43.256 --> 00:50:49.576
Salute all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints, they of Italy salute you.

00:50:49.576 --> 00:50:52.636
Grace be with you all. Amen.
